generateContCat.py:

Python code to take Astrid catalog files and generate a tmbidl
continuum file to primarily import the source positions. (The GBT
system does not provide these coordinates in any FITS file!)  The user
is prompted for the project name.The output filename is
"source_catalog".

Usage:  

> python generateContCat.py <catalog name>


Example:

fourier[316]% python generateContCat.py hii
 
Reading data from proj : hii
 
Processing catalog:  fluxcal.cat
Processing catalog:  pointing.cat
Processing catalog:  final_18-30_good.cat
Processing catalog:  final_50-65_good.cat
Processing catalog:  reobserve_30-50.cat
Processing catalog:  reobserve_30-50_continuum.cat
Processing catalog:  far_arm_nvss.cat
Processing catalog:  far_arm_2nd_tier.cat
Processing catalog:  cross_cal.cat
fourier[317]% 
